      "content": "Under the **Conflict Resolution and De-escalation** section, staff must approach disagreements with unwavering **respect** by openly acknowledging differences without dismissing the other party's perspective. When tensions rise, it is crucial to pause and practice **professionalism** in tone, focusing on the issue at hand rather than personal attributes to prevent escalation. This approach ensures that **boundaries** are held firmly so that conversations remain constructive and solution-oriented rather than becoming deflective or personal attacks.\n\nTo maintain a high safety score while providing real value, consider adding a checklist or flowchart next to this text detailing the \"5-Step De-escalation Protocol,\" which you can print for the safety audit. You can also add another example sentence in this paragraph that explicitly mentions \"maintaining boundaries\" to reinforce the keyword density the audit requires without losing the professional tone.",
